# MESSAGE: an l5p:Pack carries l5p:standing l5p:Level5 but no l5p:SabotageEvidence
# individual cites a real fail-closed proof for it. l5p:cap06 ("Generated
# negative witnesses") is one of the 12 required Level5 capabilities and its
# own l5p:capDesc demands "Sabotage/falsification fixtures ... proving the
# pack fails closed, not just that it succeeds" -- l5p:missingCap being empty
# (see .specify/gates/l5-level5-standing-requires-closed-capabilities.rq) is
# only a NEGATIVE signal: the pack's own author didn't flag cap06 as open.
# It is not a POSITIVE artifact proving a sabotage test actually ran. This
# gate adds that positive bar: at least one l5p:SabotageEvidence individual
# naming this pack via l5p:packId, with a real l5p:sabotageCommand (the
# literal command that was run) and a real l5p:sabotageResult (the literal
# observed outcome -- an actual refusal code or test-failure signature, not
# a bare assertion). Record one before setting l5p:standing to l5p:Level5.
PREFIX l5p: <http://ggen.org/l5-promotion#>
SELECT ?packId WHERE {
  ?pack a l5p:Pack ;
        l5p:packId ?packId ;
        l5p:standing l5p:Level5 .
  FILTER NOT EXISTS {
    ?ev a l5p:SabotageEvidence ;
        l5p:packId ?packId ;
        l5p:sabotageCommand ?cmd ;
        l5p:sabotageResult ?res .
  }
}
ORDER BY ?packId
